pageTitle: Los Lonely Boys concert postponed to August | Folsom Telegraph
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {25407=Carrera Productions’ sold out Los Lonely Boys concert at Three Stages in Folsom, originally scheduled for this Saturday night, has been postponed to August as the result of an accident that occurred at a concert last week in Southern California in which Henry Garza, one of the group’s members, was injured in a fall from the front of stage. Henry has been hospitalized and is recuperating under professional care. The group’s concerts through March 9 are all being rescheduled., 25905=If you are a current ticket holder, your ticket for the originally scheduled concert will be honored for the new performance date, Tuesday, Aug. 13. Alternately, if you are unable to attend the rescheduled performance, you may request a refund by contacting the Three Stages ticket office at (916) 608-6888.}
